  "text": "Just finished implementing and testing the final positioning adjustments for the emo hair asset. The hair #3 now uses data-position-x=\"60%\" and data-position-y=\"-6%\" with anchor=\"top\". The complete SVG has been optimized with:\n\n- ViewBox optimized from \"0 0 28 9\" to \"1 1 25 7\" (removed dead space)\n- Dimensions reduced from 28×9 to 25×7 pixels  \n- Stroke width reduced to 0.5 for better appearance\n- Color inheritance using currentColor\n- Z-order set to \"front\"\n- Width scaling at 125%\n\nThe anchor-based positioning system is now fully functional with three working hair styles:\n1. Cat ears (hair #1): bottom anchor at 3% with z-order \"behind\"\n2. Sweatband (hair #2): center anchor for between-body-eyes positioning \n3. Emo hair (hair #3): top anchor at 60%/-6% with 125% scaling\n\nThe generation script successfully creates 100 agents with random hair selection from indices 0, 1, 2 (representing hair styles 1, 2, 3). All positioning logic handles percentage-based coordinates with proper anchor calculations.",
  "sections": [
    "Project Notes"
  ],
